### Enrichment
Brazilian limeade (limonada suica/Swiss lemonade) is made by blending whole limes with peel, water, ice, and sweetened condensed milk. Called Swiss Lemonade because condensed milk was popularized in Brazil by Nestle. KEY TIP: Only blend 10-15 seconds to avoid bitterness from pith. Serve immediately — bitterness increases over time. The alcohol tag may be incorrect as traditional recipe is non-alcoholic.

